Besides the direct ROS-scavenging activity of NO, its beneficial effect is exerted by the regulation of the antioxidant enzymes activity that controls toxic levels of ROS and RNS (
 Uchida et al., 2002; 
 Shi et al., 2005; 
 Song et al., 2006; 
 Romero-Puertas et al., 2007; 
 Bai et al., 2011). NO can modulate cell redox balance in plants through the regulation of gene expression, posttranslational modification or by its binding to the heme prosthetic group of some antioxidant enzymes.
